   Selected Research Topics
     * Astrophysics Branch (SSA)
          + IDENTIFYING POLYCYCLIC AROMATIC HYDROCARBONS IN SPACE
            (Jesse Bregman and Pasquale Temi)
          + THE AIRES FAR INFRARED DETECTOR ARRAY
            (Edwin Erickson, Jessie Dotson, Jam Farhoomand, and
            Christopher Mason)
          + THE WORLD'S LARGEST GRATING
            (Michael R. Haas, James A. Baltz, Edwin F. Erickson, Emmett I.
            Quigley, and David C. Scimeca)
          + THE SOFIA WATER VAPOR MONITOR
            (Thomas L. Roellig, Robert Cooper, Brian Shiroyama, Regina
            Flores, Lunming Yuen, and Allan Meyer)
          + AMES NEW INTERSTELLAR SIMULATION CHAMBER CAVITY RING DOWN
            SPECTROSCOPY OF INTERSTELLAR ORGANIC MATERIALS
            (Farid Salama, Ludovic Biennier, Robert Walker, Lou
            Allamandola, Jim Scherer, and Anthony O'Keefe)
     * Astrobiology Technology Branch (SSR)
          + ADVANCED LIFE SUPPORT POWER REDUCTION
            (Cory K. Finn)
          + SOLID-STATE COMPRESSOR FOR SPACE STATION OXYGEN RECOVERY
            (John Finn)
          + DEVELOPMENT OF A WASTE PROCESSING INCINERATOR FOR LIFE SUPPORT
            (John W. Fisher)
          + DEVELOPMENT OF THE VAPOR PHASE CATALYTIC AMMONIA REMOVAL
            PROCESS
            (Michael Flynn and Bruce Borchers)
          + PROTEIN NANOTECHNOLOGY
            (Jonathan Trent)
     * Planetary Systems Branch (SST)
          + PARTICLE-GAS DYNAMICS IN THE PROTOPLANETARY NEBULA
            (J.N. Cuzzi, R.C. Hogan, and A.R. Dobrovolskis)
          + PLANETARY RINGS
            (J.N. Cuzzi, I. Mosqueira, M. Showalter, and F. Poulet)
          + VORTEX EVOLUTION IN A PROTOPLANETARY DISK
            (Sanford Davis)
          + LIQUID WATER ON PRESENT DAY MARS?
            (Robert M. Haberle)
          + THE CENTER FOR STAR FORMATION STUDIES
            (D. Hollenbach, K.R. Bell, and G. Laughlin)
          + THE FORMATION AND DYNAMICS OF PLANETARY SYSTEMS
            (Gregory Laughlin)
          + STABILITY OF UPSILON ANDROMEDAE'S PLANETARY SYSTEM
            (Jack J. Lissauer and Eugenio Rivera)
          + THE ORGANIC REFRACTORY MATERIAL IN THE DIFFUSE INTERSTELLAR
            MEDIUM: MID-IR SPECTROSCOPIC CONSTRAINTS
            (Yvonne J. Pendleton and Louis J. Allamandola)
          + CRATERING RATES ON SYNCHRONOUSLY ROTATING SATELLITES
            (Kevin Zahnle and Paul Schenk)
     * Exobiology Branch (SSX)
          + A GREENHOUSE COLLABORATORY
            (Brad Bebout and Richard Keller)
          + CHEMIN: A MINERALOGICAL INSTRUMENT FOR MARS EXPLORATION
            (David F. Blake)
          + SUGAR-RELATED COMPOUNDS IN METEORITES
            (George Cooper, Novelle Kimmich, Josh Sarinana, Katrina
            Brabham, Laurence Garrel, and Warren Belisle)
          + EFFECTS OF DISTRUBANCE ON MICROBIAL COMMUNITIES
            (Ken Cullings)
          + CARBON NANOTUBE DEPOSITION AND GROWTH TECHNIQUE
            (Lance Delzeit)
          + STRUCTURE AND FUNCTIONS OF PROTOCELLS
            (Andrew Pohorille and Michael A. Wilson)
          + MICROBIAL ECOSYSTEM STRUCTURE
            (Lee Prufert-Bebout)
          + RINGDOWN CAVITY FOR ISOTOPIC RATIO MEASUREMENTS OF CARBON AND
            OXYGEN
            (Todd Sauke and Joe Becker)
          + PREBIOTIC PEPTIDE SYNTHESIS
            (Arthur L. Weber)


